OL,6,F"We are always learning but we
OL,7,Frecognise there is more to do, which
OL,8,Fis why we have introduced systems
OL,9,Fwhere we can consistently act on
OL,10,Ffeedback and make improvements when
OL,11,Fcustomers' experiences have fallen
OL,12,Fbelow expectations."
OL,14,FIt is understood the DWP does not
OL,15,Froutinely share Internal Process
OL,16,FReviews and that they are used for
OL,17,Flearning within the organisation.
